# Project Setup and Infrastructure Guide

## Prerequisites
1. Install [Helm]
2. Install [Docker]
3. Install [Git]
4. Install [aws-cli]
5. Install [Java-21]
6. Install [Maven]

## Project Setup
1. Clone the repository:
    git clone https://github.com/gabriellfe/itau.git
    cd itau

2. Running back-end local:
    docker-compose up -d


## Infrastructure Setup
1. Create infrastructure in AWS:
    Login in AWS
        - aws configure
        - terraform init
        - terraform plan
        - terraform apply
    
## Running the Application in AWS
1. Deploy using Nginx:
    kubectl apply -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/kubernetes/ingress-nginx/main/deploy/static/provider/cloud/deploy.yaml

2. Deploy using Helm:
    Inside the file itau-helm/values.yaml:
        Change ingress host to your host

    helm install itau-eks itau-helm


## Testing
1. Run unit tests:
    cd itau-backend
    mvn test
    
## Deployment
1. Build the application:
    ```bash
    npm run build
    ```

## Destroy
1. Remove deploys
    kubectl delete all --all -n ingress-nginx

2. Remove infra
    terraform destroy 